public class EquivalentParameter
extends Parameter

Immutable specialization of a common model parameter allowing for Java equivalence relations to function in tandem with framework parameter equivalencing.

If a bucket is provided during time of construction, the equivalence relation for these objects will be based solely on the bucket field. The effect of this is that for two equivalence parameter objects: 

 
 x: (NAMESPACE1:VALUE1)
 y: (NAMESPACE2:VALUE2)
If x and y have the same bucket, i.e., they both express the same biological knowledge, the Java object representations are equal. Therefore x.equals(y) and y.equals(x). Note that for parameters with no equivalences, these objects function identically to normal Parameter objects with the exception of their immutable nature.
